parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Circuit Breaker and Stator Assembly)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system, specifically the circuit breaker and stator assembly, can cause an unexpected interruption of all electrical power to the motorcycle, leading to sudden stalling, loss of control, and potential accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Leaks at Tank Fittings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking fuel lines can cause a fire hazard, especially if the gasoline is ignited by a hot engine or exhaust pipe, potentially leading to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: fuel drips or puddles under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective fuel line fittings can cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard, especially if the gasoline is ignited by a hot engine or exhaust pipe, potentially leading to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: fuel drips or puddles under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Tire Inspection during Scheduled Maintenance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly inspect tires during scheduled maintenance can lead to tire failure, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Tires may be worn beyond safe limits

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incomplete or misrepresented scheduled maintenance can lead to overlooked safety issues, potentially causing accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: Consumers may not be aware of necessary repairs or maintenance
service records may be incomplete or inaccurate
or consumers may experience unexpected vehicle failures.
